{"tid":308491,"cid":4,"subCid":0,"title":"［突發] iphone 8 放棄 Touch ID","createTime":"2017-07-04T08:03:19.000Z","updateTime":"2019-05-11T07:04:25.000Z","uid":31208,"like":6,"dislike":45,"uniUserReply":0,"replies":[{"pid":"af3b8f44711b3b6044ab3eb27bf592876778504d","tid":308491,"uid":31208,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-07-04T08:03:19.000Z","msg":"&quot;We predict the OLED model won&rsquo;t support fingerprint recognition, reasons being: (1) the full-screen design doesn&rsquo;t work with existing capacitive fingerprint recognition, and (2) the scan-through ability of the under-display fingerprint solution still has technical challenges, including: (i) requirement for a more complex panel pixel design; (ii) disappointing scan-through of OLED panel despite it being thinner than LCD panel; and (iii) weakened scan-through performance due to overlayered panel module. As the new OLED iPhone won&rsquo;t support under-display fingerprint recognition, we now do not expect production ramp-up will be delayed again (we previously projected the ramp-up would be postponed to late October or later).&quot;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2017/07/03/ming-chi-kuo-iphone-omit-touch-id/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.macrumors.com%2F2017%2F07%2F03%2Fming-chi-kuo-iphone-omit-touch-id%2F&d=rnN3sZUNEYpahFPz0GwFH4zu7PIJYhBZqlGrkalTKs4%3D&h=9a86360a\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.macrumors.com/2017/07/03/ming-chi-kuo-iphone-omit-touch-id/</a>"},{"pid":"85d5d0e48b9faf2d50ab243d3062995157a8ce32","tid":308491,"uid":31254,"like":18,"dislike":0,"score":18,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-07-04T08:25:10.000Z","msg":"apple已死"},{"pid":"29b2362310845a65dd79eee9c99a38e03a283804","tid":308491,"uid":3773,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-07-04T08:42:25.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dislike.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"cfa652d2c69421d97aa0ce9cac4db4a0251fb15b","tid":308491,"uid":133,